{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/event-driven-sdk-with-coroutines","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<hr>\n<p>For this study note in particular I want to explore a little bit of the asynchronous feature provided by Kotlin, a.k.a <a href=\"https://kotlinlang.org/docs/coroutines-overview.html\">coroutines</a>, and using it on the android platform.</p>\n<p>Most Android applications work with many asynchronous components, and build a solid communication between them is a way of maintaining the application state in control. The idea here is to use coroutines to create a simple SDK that handles event broadcasting between any components in the application, an asynchronous message-passing system based on the Event-Driven Architecture (or EventBus).</p>\n<p>This type of architecture utilizes the Publisher-Subscriber pattern having consumers of some event subscribing to receive the event and the producers publishing the event. Each consumer that subscribes to an event will listen to a channel that delivers the event immediately when the producer publishes it.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cstiano/cstiano.github.io/source/src/images/pub-sub-diagram.png\" alt=\"Publisher-Subscriber diagram\"></p>\n<p>So, first things first, what will be the name of the project? The first thing that pops in my head was \"spine\", as an analogy to spinal column, but I looked in github and already exists a <a href=\"https://github.com/spine/spine\">project</a> with this name. So I just included stream in it and we have the name: spine-stream (SS).</p>\n<p>Before starting to thought about the structure of the project I search for existent libs with the same purpose and I found <a href=\"https://github.com/greenrobot/EventBus\">EventBus</a> (java), <a href=\"https://github.com/deva666/EventHub\">EventHub</a> (java), and <a href=\"https://github.com/adrielcafe/Broker\">Broker</a> (kotlin). I liked the strategy that each one of these took and inspires me to compare to what I wanted to spine-stream.</p>\n<p>One think that could cause problems is managing subscriptions, that situation when you forgot to call the function that unsubscribes the channel when the process finish, all three libs have that. </p>\n<p>I wanted to spine-stream to manage the subscriptions in the background, and those who use just have to call the subscription function and the lib unsubscribes itself when the process finishes. So for the functionalities, I wanted to be necessary just call one method (plug and play), without managing subscriptions or setting up contexts for the subscription. A spoiler of the final usage:</p>\n<pre class=\"grvsc-container default-dark\" data-language=\"java\" data-index=\"0\"><code class=\"grvsc-code\"><span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk3\">// MainActivity</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\"> override fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">onCreate</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(savedInstanceState</span><span class=\"mtk15\">:</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> Bundle</span><span class=\"mtk15\">?</span><span class=\"mtk1\">) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span><span class=\"mtk4\">super</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">onCreate</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(savedInstanceState)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span><span class=\"mtk11\">setContentView</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk12\">R</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">layout</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">activity_main</span><span class=\"mtk1\">)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span><span class=\"mtk12\">SpineStream</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">subscribe</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&lt;UserInfo&gt; { event </span><span class=\"mtk4\">-&gt;</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Log</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">d</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(TAG, </span><span class=\"mtk8\">&quot;Received user: $event&quot;</span><span class=\"mtk1\">)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">}</span></span></span></code></pre>\n<pre class=\"grvsc-container default-dark\" data-language=\"java\" data-index=\"1\"><code class=\"grvsc-code\"><span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk3\">// UserService</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">override fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">onStart</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(intent</span><span class=\"mtk15\">:</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> Intent</span><span class=\"mtk15\">?</span><span class=\"mtk1\">, startId</span><span class=\"mtk15\">:</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> Int) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span><span class=\"mtk4\">super</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">onStart</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(intent, startId)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span><span class=\"mtk12\">SpineStream</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">publish</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(userInfo)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">}</span></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>So I defined the requisites for the initial version 0.1.0 to be the following: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Broadcast events from any component;</li>\n<li>Only have the publish and subscribe interfaces;</li>\n<li>Manage the broadcast channels in background, to support the workarounds with simple interfaces (no need to deal with channel registration and unsubscription);</li>\n<li>Attach the channel manager to the application lifecycle;</li>\n<li>The events can be any type of data object;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A way of transfer events with coroutines is by using the broadcast channels primitives. Coroutines provide some different types of broadcast channels and I tested them to make sure which one I going to use in SS. For that, I made a playground test suite on my project to see the behavior of each Broadcast Channel. The tests was made based on this tutorial.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Channel</strong> - have a relation of one to one, meaning that the producer will send the event for one consumer, in the scenario when you have many consumers, the produced event is received by the first consumer and all other ones will not get the event.</li>\n<li><strong>BroadcastChannel</strong> - different from the Channel, the BroadcastChannel assures that all consumers subscribed in the channel receives the event emitted by the producer (one to many relation).</li>\n<li><strong>ConflatedBroadcastChannel</strong> - this one is similar to BroacastChannel, enabling many subscribers, but it assures that the consumers will only receives the most recent event emitted.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For the general purpose that I wanted I ended up choosing the BroadcastChannel which delivers all events published, considering the buffer configured, and all subscribers will receive the events. So having the main tool decided I considered the following structure for the project.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cstiano/cstiano.github.io/source/src/images/spine-stream-diag.png\" alt=\"SpineStream diagram\"></p>\n<p>The SS architecture are composed by <em>1)</em> an init module, that going to initialize the channels and attach the SDK to the application lifecycle; <em>2)</em> A channel manager attached to the application lifecycle responsible for flush the channels when necessary; <em>3)</em> The handler that implements the publisher and subscriber interfaces, containing the logic to exchange events through the channels; <em>4)</em> The SpineStream model makes public the interfaces as a static class.</p>\n<p>For this module in particular I wanted to test an initialization using Content Provider. The Android Content Provider is a component that supplies content/data between different applications and can be useful to initialize SDKs. Acknowledging these aspects, the approach applying content provider eliminates the necessity of calling an init method by who is using the SDK. So I made a <strong>InitProvider</strong> extending from the ContentProvider.</p>\n<pre class=\"grvsc-container default-dark\" data-language=\"java\" data-index=\"2\"><code class=\"grvsc-code\"><span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk4\">abstract</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk4\">class</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk10\">InitProvider</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> : ContentProvider() {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    override final fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">insert</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk12\">uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">, </span><span class=\"mtk12\">values</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">ContentValues</span><span class=\"mtk1\">?): Uri? = null</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    override final fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">query</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">projection</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk10\">Array</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mtk10\">out</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk10\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&gt;?,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">selection</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">?,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">selectionArgs</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk10\">Array</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mtk10\">out</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk10\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&gt;?,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">sortOrder</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">?</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    ): Cursor? = null</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    override final fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">getType</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk12\">uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">): String? = null</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    override final fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">update</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">values</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">ContentValues</span><span class=\"mtk1\">?,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">selection</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">?,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">selectionArgs</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk10\">Array</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mtk10\">out</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk10\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&gt;?</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    ): Int = 0</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    override final fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">delete</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Uri</span><span class=\"mtk1\">,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">selection</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">?,</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">selectionArgs</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk10\">Array</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mtk10\">out</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk10\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&gt;?</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    ): Int = 0</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">}</span></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>The init module attaches the ChannelsManager to the application lifecycle. To make this attachment it was used the ProcessLifecycleOwner, which dispatches specific triggers to an observer module regarding lifecycle steps (e.g: ON_START). If you want a more profound understanding of ProcessLifecycleOwner, take a look at the documentation. I considerer this version of SS to be used only on foreground cycles, so ProcessLifecycleOwner fits well with the purpose, because SS just need to know when the application enters at the OnStop state to refresh the in used channels.</p>\n<pre class=\"grvsc-container default-dark\" data-language=\"java\" data-index=\"3\"><code class=\"grvsc-code\"><span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk4\">class</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk10\">SpineStreamInitProvider</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> : InitProvider() {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    override fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">onCreate</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(): Boolean {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk11\">initSpineStreamSDK</span><span class=\"mtk1\">()</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk15\">return</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk4\">true</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span><span class=\"mtk4\">private</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">initSpineStreamSDK</span><span class=\"mtk1\">() {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk15\">if</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> (</span><span class=\"mtk12\">BuildConfig</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">DEBUG</span><span class=\"mtk1\">) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">            </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Log</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">d</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk8\">&quot;SpineStreamSDK&quot;</span><span class=\"mtk1\">, </span><span class=\"mtk8\">&quot;Initializing Spine Stream SDK&quot;</span><span class=\"mtk1\">)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">ProcessLifecycleOwner</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">get</span><span class=\"mtk1\">().</span><span class=\"mtk12\">lifecycle</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">addObserver</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk11\">ChannelsManager</span><span class=\"mtk1\">())</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">}</span></span></span></code></pre>\n<pre class=\"grvsc-container default-dark\" data-language=\"java\" data-index=\"4\"><code class=\"grvsc-code\"><span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk4\">class</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk10\">ChannelsManager</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> : LifecycleObserver {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    init {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">SharedChannels</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">createChannels</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk10\">ConcurrentHashMap</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&lt;String, </span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">                                        </span><span class=\"mtk10\">BroadcastChannel</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&lt;Any&gt;&gt;(DEFAULT_CAPACITY))</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    @</span><span class=\"mtk10\">OnLifecycleEvent</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk12\">Lifecycle</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">Event</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">ON_STOP</span><span class=\"mtk1\">)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">onStop</span><span class=\"mtk1\">() {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk15\">if</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> (</span><span class=\"mtk12\">BuildConfig</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">DEBUG</span><span class=\"mtk1\">) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">            </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Log</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">d</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk8\">&quot;SpineStreamSDK&quot;</span><span class=\"mtk1\">, </span><span class=\"mtk8\">&quot;onStop Channel Spine Stream SDK&quot;</span><span class=\"mtk1\">)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        val channels = </span><span class=\"mtk12\">SharedChannels</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">provideChannels</span><span class=\"mtk1\">()</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk15\">for</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> (channel in channels) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">            </span><span class=\"mtk12\">channel</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">value</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">cancel</span><span class=\"mtk1\">()</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">            </span><span class=\"mtk12\">channel</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">value</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">close</span><span class=\"mtk1\">()</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">channels</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">clear</span><span class=\"mtk1\">()</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">}</span></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>The Handler module is the core of spine-stream, which deals directly with the publishing/subscribing operations. To manage different types of data classes, the handler uses a hash map that bind the class name to a specific channel, which is created if there is no channel for that data class when the sub or pub methods was called. The coroutines make the events broadcast with BroadcastChannels and uses only background context to make sure that the event exchanges doesn't interfere on the mainThread.</p>\n<pre class=\"grvsc-container default-dark\" data-language=\"java\" data-index=\"5\"><code class=\"grvsc-code\"><span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">open </span><span class=\"mtk4\">class</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk10\">Handler</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> : Publisher, Subscriber {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    @</span><span class=\"mtk10\">VisibleForTesting</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    val channels by lazy { </span><span class=\"mtk12\">SharedChannels</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">provideChannels</span><span class=\"mtk1\">() }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    override fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">publish</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk12\">event</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Any</span><span class=\"mtk1\">) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        val className = event</span><span class=\"mtk15\">::</span><span class=\"mtk12\">class</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">toString</span><span class=\"mtk1\">()</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk11\">createChannelIfNecessary</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(className)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">GlobalScope</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">launch</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">            channels[className]</span><span class=\"mtk15\">?</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">send</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(event)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    override fun &lt;</span><span class=\"mtk10\">T</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> : </span><span class=\"mtk10\">Any</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&gt; </span><span class=\"mtk11\">subscribe</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk12\">eventClass</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk10\">KClass</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mtk10\">T</span><span class=\"mtk1\">&gt;, </span><span class=\"mtk12\">onEvent</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">suspend</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> (T) -&gt; </span><span class=\"mtk12\">Unit</span><span class=\"mtk1\">) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        val className = </span><span class=\"mtk12\">eventClass</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">toString</span><span class=\"mtk1\">()</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk11\">createChannelIfNecessary</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(className)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk12\">GlobalScope</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk12\">launch</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">            channels[className]</span><span class=\"mtk15\">?</span><span class=\"mtk1\">.</span><span class=\"mtk11\">openSubscription</span><span class=\"mtk1\">().</span><span class=\"mtk12\">let</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> { channel </span><span class=\"mtk4\">-&gt;</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">                </span><span class=\"mtk15\">if</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> (channel != </span><span class=\"mtk4\">null</span><span class=\"mtk1\">) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">                    </span><span class=\"mtk15\">for</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> (event in channel) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">                        </span><span class=\"mtk11\">onEvent</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(event as T)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">                    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">                }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">            }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    </span><span class=\"mtk4\">private</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> fun </span><span class=\"mtk11\">createChannelIfNecessary</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(</span><span class=\"mtk12\">eventClassName</span><span class=\"mtk1\">: </span><span class=\"mtk12\">String</span><span class=\"mtk1\">) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        </span><span class=\"mtk15\">if</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> (channels[eventClassName] == </span><span class=\"mtk4\">null</span><span class=\"mtk1\">) {</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">            channels[eventClassName] = </span><span class=\"mtk11\">BroadcastChannel</span><span class=\"mtk1\">(DEFAULT_CAPACITY)</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">        }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">    }</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"mtk1\">}</span></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>As a conclusion, the purpose here was to implement an event-driven SDK as simple as possible to play with coroutines, as an extra I can evolve this project increasing other features, or integrate it in other project that fits with this requisites. This project have a overhead of implementation by including an init module with content provider, but it something that I wanted to test. There is others types of event-driven like implementations for android (or using a publish-subscriber logic, e.g: LiveData), and there is pro and cons of using this logic, but this discussion isn't in the scope here. You can look the spine-stream source code <a href=\"https://www.github.com/cstiano/spine-stream\">here</a>.</p>\n<hr>\n<h4>References</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://proandroiddev.com/discovering-event-driven-architecture-for-android-717e6332065e\">Discovering Event-Driven Architecture for Android</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://guides.codepath.com/android/creating-content-providers\">Creating Content Providers | CodePath Android Cliffnotes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.raywenderlich.com/books/kotlin-coroutines-by-tutorials/v2.0/chapters/12-broadcast-channels\">Broadcast Channels - raywenderlich</a></li>\n</ul>\n<style class=\"grvsc-styles\">\n  .grvsc-container {\n    overflow: auto;\n    position: relative;\n    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;\n    padding-top: 1rem;\n    padding-top: var(--grvsc-padding-top, var(--grvsc-